# SCSS/Sass Development Conventions

## File Structure

- [src/styles/main.scss](mdc:src/styles/main.scss) - Main entry point
- [src/styles/vendor.scss](mdc:src/styles/vendor.scss) - Third-party styles
- [src/styles/\_variabls.scss](mdc:src/styles/_variabls.scss) - Global variables
- [src/styles/\_mixin.scss](mdc:src/styles/_mixin.scss) - Mixins and functions
- [src/styles/\_common.scss](mdc:src/styles/_common.scss) - Common/base styles

## Component-Specific Styles

Each page/component has its own SCSS file:

- `_header.scss`, `_footer.scss` - Layout components
- `_product.scss`, `_cart.scss` - E-commerce specific
- `_hero.scss`, `_banner.scss` - Landing page sections

## Best Practices

- Use SCSS partials (files starting with `_`)
- Import Bootstrap as vendor dependency
- Follow BEM methodology for class naming
- Use variables for colors, fonts, and spacing
- Organize imports in logical order: variables → mixins → base → components

## Build Output

- Compiled to: `build/css/main.css`
- Source maps generated for debugging
- Autoprefixer applied for browser compatibility
- CSS minification in production builds
